eNCA's Heidi Giokos explained. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Mango Airlines could be grounded by 1 May. An internal notice sent to the carrier's staff has been seen by eNCA. READ: Mango reaches an agreement with SAA Technical Lessors are demanding payment from the Public Enterprises Department and they want Mango planes grounded if they don't receive their money. Mango technical support, as well as SAA technical support, was suspended due to non-payment in September last year.